title: 10 Examples of Chemical Changes We Experience...
text:
By Anne Marie Helmenstine, Ph.D. Updated October 16, 2016 . 
Chemical changes involve chemical reactions and the creation of new products. Typically, a chemical change is irreversible. In contrast, physical changes do not form new products and are reversible.This is a list of more than 10 examples of chemical changes. rusting of iron metabolism of food in the body mixing an acid and a base, such as hydrochloric acid (HCl) and sodium hydroxide (NaOH) cooking an egg digesting sugar with the amylase in saliva mixing baking soda and vinegar to produce carbon dioxide gas baking a cake
